hopobject.body: What do you want to do when you've finished? astroglide usage Healthcare.gov is the entry site for consumers in 36 states that have chosen not to build their own healthcare exchanges. The website was hobbled within minutes of its launch on October 1. HHS attributed the crash to an unexpected surge of millions of interested consumers seeking information on the new benefits, and said it was working to address capacity and software problems to quickly fix the problem.
